'''Avalere Health''' is a consulting firm headquartered in [[Washington, D.C.]], specializing in strategy, policy, and data analysis for life sciences, health plans and providers. The company also publishes research studies on health care issues and the [[health care reform debate in the United States]].
==History==
Avalere was founded as The Health Strategies Consultancy LLC in 2000 by [[Dan Mendelson]]. The company was renamed Avalere Health in 2005, and in 2008 Mendelson sold a minority interest to [[ABS Capital Partners]], a [[Baltimore, Maryland]]–based private equity firm.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.techjournal.org/2008/04/marylands-abs-capital-partners-buys-minority-stake-in-dcs-avalere/ |title=Maryland’s ABS Capital Partners Buys Minority Stake in D.C.'s Avalere |work=TechJournal |date=April 29, 2008 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150530001731/http://www.techjournal.org/2008/04/marylands-abs-capital-partners-buys-minority-stake-in-dcs-avalere/ |archivedate=2015-05-30 |df= }}</ref> In September 2015, Avalere was purchased by [[Inovalon]], a technology company providing cloud-based analytics and intervention platforms to the healthcare industry.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.inovalon.com/press-releases/2015/inovalon-completes-previously-announced-acquisition-avalere |title=Inovalon Completes Previously Announced Acquisition of Avalere |work=Inovalon |date=September 1, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite press release |url=http://avalere.com/news/avalere-joins-inovalon |title=Avalere Joins Inovalon |work=Avalere |date=September 1, 2015}}</ref> Avalere continues to operate as a subsidiary with a focus on providing advisory services on market consolidation, cost management, quality improvement, and [[managed care]] as well as business intelligence and corporate communication strategies. The firm has also published studies on drug plan coverage and managed care plans in the US.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/wonkblog/wp/2015/03/13/how-expensive-medications-are-increasingly-out-of-reach/ |title=How expensive medications are increasingly out of reach |work=The Washington Post |date=March 31, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/09/18/business/concern-grows-over-cost-of-drugs-under-new-health-care-law.html |title=Concern Over Drug Costs |work=The New York Times |date=September 17, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first=Michelle |last=Andrews |url=https://www.npr.org/sections/health-shots/2014/10/03/353256972/what-you-need-to-know-for-medicare-open-enrollment |title=What You Need to Know for Medicare Open Enrollment |department=Your Health |publisher=NPR |agency=Kaiser Health News |date=October 3, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/brucejapsen/2014/12/17/private-insurers-net-9-3-million-from-acas-medicaid-expansion/ |title=Private Insurers Net 9.3 Million from ACA's Medicaid Expansion |work=Forbes |date=December 17, 2014}}</ref>
