'''Hearing level''' is the [[sound pressure]] level produced by an [[audiometer]] at a specific frequency. It is measured in [[decibel]]s with reference to audiometric zero.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Audiogram|url=http://www.vanasch.school.nz/pdfs/audiogram.pdf|publisher=VanAsh Deaf Education Center|accessdate=16 December 2012}}</ref> Hearing of speech is considered to be impaired   when the hearing level is shifted 25 dB or more.<ref>{{cite web|last=Truax|first=Barry|title=Hearing level|url=https://www.sfu.ca/sonic-studio/handbook/Hearing_Level.html|work=Handbook for acoustic ecology|publisher=SFA|accessdate=16 December 2012}}</ref>

